latestIgtvVideos.title: MOVING IN 🏡
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
3 months back we decided to move out, randomly just to study! @heenakazii and I decided to look for houses on our own without involving our parents cause we wanted to ‘adult’ the right way 😂🤦🏻‍♀️ which turned out to be a night mare for 10 days looking at houses which we couldn’t step in, meeting owners who were suuuuppper bitchy until I finally sat down to be friends w our broker and convinced him to show us a house according to our choices and to my surprise the next house was IT!! The moment we got in, I remember looking at heena and we knew we had to get this!!! Then began allll the crazy that I’d never even imagined would be waiting for us. Right from setting up the house, to looking for a house help, to cooking, studying, working out, dressing up, crying, groceries, we’ve done it all. 
PS- You’re too lucky if you stay w me 🤪 I can entertain you w my bullshit 24/7 😂❤️. While @heenakazii is the mom of the house who can’t stop yelling & @khanariba26 is the warmth in the house who’ll do everything for you before you even ask, and I’m the one who just entertains 😂 I’d not have it any other way!!!! Ofcourse all creds go to my unpaid photographer @heenakazii😂❤️. Can’t wait for the lockdown to end so I can squish y’all again in our beautiful house❤️

If you are having excessive hairfall then you need to consider these blood tests to help you understand the underlying cause! 

1) vitamin B 12 : essential for DNA, RNA & protein synthesis which is very crucial for hair follicle growth. 

2) Vitamin D: regulates the hair growth cycle & deficiency leads to alopecia. 

3) ferritin : iron stores , low levels reduce oxygen supply to hair roots causing shedding. 

4) Haemoglobin (Complete Blood Count- CBC) : low haemoglobin indicates anaemia, a common cause of hair loss. 

5) Thyroid profile TSH, T3, T4 : Thyroid imbalances disrupt hair growth & lead to thinning or shedding of hair. 

6) Zinc levels : Zinc supports hair tissue growth and repair, deficiency weakens follicles. 

7) Serum testosterone + DHT : Elevated levels can shrink hair follicles and trigger androgenetic alopecia. 

8) Folic acid (vitamin B9) : Supports healthy cell division and promotes hair regeneration. 

9) Liver function test : Poor liver function affects detoxification and nutrient metabolism, impacting hair health. 

10) Hormone panel (FSH, LH, Estrogen, Progesterone) - especially in women. Imbalances can lead to hair thinning or pattern baldness.
